uk.ac.soton.simulation.jsit.core

Class DistributionCategorical<C extends java.lang.Enum<C>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.soton.simulation.jsit.core.AbstractStochasticItem
      • uk.ac.soton.simulation.jsit.core.Distribution

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DistBernoulli, DistCustomCategorical, DistUniformDiscrete

    public abstract class DistributionCategorical<C extends java.lang.Enum<C>>
extends DistributionDiscrete
implements java.io.Serializable
    JSIT abstract representation of all categorical distributions. The categories can either be a Java enum and/or numbered outcomes 1-K which can be mapped to a sequence of integer ranges [a,b] (where there should be K entries across all the ranges). The nested Range class represents those ranges.
    Since:
    0.1
    Author:
    Stuart Rossiter

      • addRange

        public int addRange(int min,
                    int max)
        Add a range to be used as part of mapping sampled outcomes to an integer. Ranges are applied in the order added; e.g., adding [1,2] and [5,6] ranges means that the 4 possible outcomes map to 1,2,5 and 6 respectively. The distribution should be locked prior to adding the first such range, and unlocked after the last is added (at which point it will be checked that the sequence of ranges includes K elements).
        Parameters:
        min - The range minimum.
        max - The range maximum.
        Returns:
        The number of entries across all ranges added so far. (This should equal K when the last range is added.)
        Since:
        0.1

      • clearRanges

        public void clearRanges()
